snippet.textDisplay: @SupraDarky One of the most memorable moments I have with this song is being stuck on top of a tree with mobs (enemies) on the beach below, my fortress a bit too far to get to, and dangerous on top of a hill. It started playing just before the sun was rising, and it was such a peaceful moment that got me reflecting about a lot. Despite being a poorly texturized sun, it was one of the most beautiful moments the game ever presented for me. If I can recommend any game to you, Supra, it's this one.

snippet.textDisplay: It's kind of silly to talk about the way minceraft "used to be", but I can't help but feel sad knowing I will never feel the same way I had when I first started playing this game. I played the creative mode for hours a day, even staying up all night to work on a building. I finally bought the game, and I remebmer the first cave I found, when I moved into another cave, and the first time hearing skeletons burning outside. It's not the same. That file is gone, and I can never relive it when I try.
